                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 11.765,
                                "byte_start": 80909,
                                "byte_stop": 128034,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 86-489, Langley versus Federal Deposit Insurance Company will be announced by Justice Scalia."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 11.765,
                        "stop": 186.07,
                        "byte_start": 128034,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15049,
                            "name": "Antonin Scalia",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/antonin_scalia",
                            "last_name": "Scalia",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2693,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 528094800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2693"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32678,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 58944,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/antonin_scalia_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 10699,
                            "identifier": "antonin_scalia"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 11.765,
                                "stop": 16.071,
                                "byte_start": 128034,
                                "byte_stop": 145275,
                                "text": "This case comes here on a petition for writ of certiorari to the Fifth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 16.071,
                                "stop": 47.055,
                                "byte_start": 145275,
                                "byte_stop": 269200,
                                "text": "12 U.S.C. Section 1823(e) provides that no agreement maybe asserted to diminish the right title or interest of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation in an asset unless the agreement is 1) In writing; 2) Executed contemporaneously with the insured bank\u0027s acquisition of that interest; 3) Approved in the minutes of the bank\u0027s board of directors or loan committee; and 4) Continuously from its execution, an official record of the bank."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.055,
                                "stop": 57.157,
                                "byte_start": 269200,
                                "byte_stop": 309637,
                                "text": "The petitioners here executed a note payable to an FDIC insured bank in consideration for a loan which they used to purchase real estate."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 57.157,
                                "stop": 72.665,
                                "byte_start": 309637,
                                "byte_stop": 371600,
                                "text": "When the bank sued for payment of the note, the petitioners asserted as a defense that the bank had procured the note by misrepresenting the amount of the land and the mineral acres it contained in the absence of outstanding mineral leases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 72.665,
                                "stop": 82.694,
                                "byte_start": 371600,
                                "byte_stop": 411724,
                                "text": "No references to this representations appeared in the documents executed by the petitioners, in the bank\u0027s records, or in the minutes of the bank\u0027s board of directors or loan committee."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.694,
                                "stop": 86.383,
                                "byte_start": 411724,
                                "byte_stop": 426457,
                                "text": "The bank was later closed because of its unsound financial condition."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 86.383,
                                "stop": 91.548,
                                "byte_start": 426457,
                                "byte_stop": 447146,
                                "text": "The FDIC was appointed as receiver and the FDIC acquired the note."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 91.548,
                                "stop": 96.092,
                                "byte_start": 447146,
                                "byte_stop": 465327,
                                "text": "The FDIC was later substituted as plaintiff in this lawsuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 96.092,
                                "stop": 107.314,
                                "byte_start": 465327,
                                "byte_stop": 510258,
                                "text": "FDIC moved for summary judgment on the ground that the petitioners\u0027 misrepresentation defense constituted an agreement that did not meet the requirements of 12 U.S.C. 1823(e)."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 107.314,
                                "stop": 112.896,
                                "byte_start": 510258,
                                "byte_stop": 532514,
                                "text": "The District Court granted the motion and the Fifth Circuit affirmed, we granted the petition for certiorari."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.896,
                                "stop": 123.951,
                                "byte_start": 532514,
                                "byte_stop": 576818,
                                "text": "We hold today that a condition to payment of the note including the truth of an express warranty is part of the agreement to which the requirements of 1823(e) attach."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 123.951,
                                "stop": 133.74,
                                "byte_start": 576818,
                                "byte_stop": 615897,
                                "text": "The word \u0022agreement\u0022 as used in commercial or contract law often has a wider meaning than just promise and embraces such a condition upon performance."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 133.74,
                                "stop": 157.692,
                                "byte_start": 615897,
                                "byte_stop": 711714,
                                "text": "That common meaning must be assigned to agreement in 1823(e) in order for that section to achieve its purpose of allowing federal and state bank examiners to rely on the bank\u0027s records insuring mature consideration of unusual loan transactions by senior bank officials and preventing fraudulent insertion of new terms with the collusion of bank employees when a bank appears headed for failure."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.692,
                                "stop": 173.21,
                                "byte_start": 711714,
                                "byte_stop": 773781,
                                "text": "We reject as contrary to the statute\u0027s language and these purposes, petitioners suggestions that the presence of fraud and the inducement where the FDIC\u0027s knowledge of the defense prior to acquiring the note renders what would otherwise be an agreement not an agreement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 173.21,
                                "stop": 182.412,
                                "byte_start": 773781,
                                "byte_stop": 810561,
                                "text": "Because of the representations alleged by the petitioners constituted condition on repayment and did not meet Section 1823(d)\u0027s requirements, summary judgment was properly granted."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 182.412,
                                "stop": 183.871,
                                "byte_start": 810561,
                                "byte_stop": 816413,
                                "text": "We therefore affirm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 183.871,
                                "stop": 186.07,
                                "byte_start": 816413,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Court\u0027s opinion is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
